[DhtmlXQ_comment4]"When you study and analyze GM Wan's games against the Angel's Pawn, you would find that he would play the central elephant most of the time. With this same direction counter, you know that he has prepared well for this match."[/DhtmlXQ_comment4]
[DhtmlXQ_comment10]"By retreating the cannon to the throat rank, black can prevent red from playing R8+8, and also play H8+7 to protect the pawn that has crossed the river. It is a multi-purposed move. It looks like in this game, GM Wan has prepared much since he deliberately chose to tackle an opening that he was relatively unfamiliar with."[/DhtmlXQ_comment10]
